===Talking to Prince Itzla or Servius===
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Ah, there you are. Nilsal, adventurer. I don't believe you've properly met my father. This is Servius, the Teokan of Ralos and the man whose life you saved.
* '''Player:''' Your father? I didn't realise you were related.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Yes, very fun stuff. All a bit of a convoluted mess as well! I'll be sure to tell you all about it at some point. For now though, [player name], meet Servius. Servius, meet [player name].
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' Nilsal, my child. It is an honour to meet you. Were it not for you, I may well already be making my journey to Mictl. On behalf of both myself and Ralos, I thank you.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Well let's not start celebrating just yet. There's a reason why we're lurking in this crypt.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Sorry about that, by the way. I'd have much rather given you a proper welcome on your arrival, but given the situation, it's probably best we take a bit more care.
* '''Player:''' It's not a problem. Although, I did have an interesting encounter on my way here.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Ah, the Tullus twins. Fascinating pair, aren't they?
* '''Player:''' Actually, I was talking about Metzli. I met her upstairs.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Oh, you met her! My deepest sympathies.
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' Metzli and her sect play an essential role in our lives. You should not judge her so harshly.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' You're quite right, of course. But anyway, shall we get down to business?
* '''Player:''' Sounds like a plan.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Kuani! So we have quite the predicament on our hands. My mother isn't too happy, oddly enough, and has tasked me with sorting it all out.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Someone wants our dear Teokan dead, and we have no idea who! All we know is that they were a Varlamorian.
* '''Player:''' A Varlamorian who had access to the mainland before the treaty was signed. Surely that limits the options a fair bit?
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Right you are, [player name]! In fact, it limits them to just the members of our little delegation. In other words, myself, Servius, the Tullus twins and our retinue of knights.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Now I don't think it was me... and I'm guessing you didn't try to arrange your own assassination, Servius?
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' I'd like to think I'd have done a better job if I had.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Too right. Very sloppy work. A top example of how not to assassinate someone. Still, probably best we track them down all the same.
* '''Player:''' So that leaves the Tullus twins and the knights.
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' Ennius and Furia are loyal children of Ralos. They would not wish to see my death.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Those knights should also be loyal children of Ralos, but I agree, they are far more likely candidates. Let us investigate them and see what we can find.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Servius, until we have this matter sorted, you should remain here in the capital. The palace will be the safest place.
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' Nonsense! I am the Teokan of Ralos and I have a duty to the people. I must return to the Teomat at once!
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' The Teomat does not offer the protection of the palace. You'll be an easy target there.
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' I am the chosen messenger of Ralos. He would not have me cower and hide. I will return to the Teomat.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Well this is a terrible idea that's definitely going to blow up in all our faces later, but it seems you have made your decision. However, I insist that you let me personally accompany you.
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' My child, I would be delighted to have you as a travelling companion.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' [player name], since Servius here seems keen on letting this killer have another go, you'll need to investigate the knights on your own.
* '''Player:''' I'm sure I can manage that.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Kuani! Head up to the palace and find the Tullus twins. They dealt with all the fun admin work. They'll know where those knights can be found.
* '''Player:''' I'll get to it right away.
* '''Prince Itzla Arkan:''' Then it sounds like we're all set. Timoiva, and may the sun light your way!
* '''Servius, Teokan of Ralos:''' Timoiva, my child.
* {{tact|end}}

